	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 26th 1:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some tips on the Black Dire.<br><br>I have yet to see him spawn on a set schedule as suggested on many sites.  Only real chance you have is to kill the advisor or wait for another group to kill him.<br><br>Once he spawns, have your group gather at the zone and invis.  Once ready, have the puller agro the Dire then run to zone.  Once there, the Dire will not walk away, yet all the other mobs will.  Have puller zone back in.  You can buff and prepare for battle right beside the Dire since he cons kindly.<br><br>Dire will resist most spells.  Only way to take him is to overpower him.  Nothing special on the take down, he's just another mob...with about 10k hitpoints, a 550+ HT, and double attacks around 200.<br><br>Group I was in that accomplished this task?<br>1 45 Shaman (healed, used pet, nuked)<br>1 51 Shadowknight (HT, tank, used pet)<br>1 52 Druid (nuked, healed)<br>1 40 Druid (healed)<br>1 39 Ranger (tank)<br>So, no uber group is needed to kill him, just use the tactics above to get him by himself.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
